            <thetext>This is a reminder bug for a issue in FireBug reported at http://code.google.com/p/fbug/issues/detail?id=3389

The &quot;error&quot; method does ignore newline characters. All other methods (&quot;info&quot;, &quot;debug&quot; and &quot;warn&quot;) format the output correctly.

--snip--
var items = [ &quot;foo&quot;, &quot;bar&quot;, &quot;baz&quot; ];
var message = items.join(&quot;\n&quot;);

console.info(message);
console.debug(message);
console.warn(message);
console.error(message);
--snip--

This issue does affect the output of stacktraces as error messages.</thetext>
